            <title>[SYNAPSE-652] Axis2MessageContext#getEndpoint Throws NPE for Non-Existing Endpoint Keys</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-652</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Logic is currently implemented as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            Endpoint e = getConfiguration().getEndpoint(key);&lt;br/&gt;
            synchronized (e) {&lt;br/&gt;
                if (!e.isInitialized()) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                    e.init(synEnv);
                }
&lt;p&gt;            }&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If &apos;e&apos; is null (which is the case if the key does not exist) this throws an NPE&lt;/p&gt;</description>
